			<h2>What are Small Friend and Big Friend?</h2>
			<p>Small Friend and Big Friend are fun ways of describing pairs of complementary numbers that add up to 5 and 10 respectively. Any number between 5 and zero have a Small Friend. For example, the Small Friend of 3 is 2 because they sum together to make 5. Any number between 10 and zero have a Big Friend. For example, the Big Friend of 4 is 6 because they sum together to make 10. An understanding of these basic math skills are a requirement for learning abacus and will become deep-rooted through daily worksheet practice.</p>
