			<p>The abacus is made up of columns of beads with each column representing a digit (0 - 9). The relative position of each column indicates its decimal position. For example, one column represents 1's, the column to its left represents 10's and the column to it's left represents 100's.</p>

			<p>To determine what digit is represented, bead position is examined.
			Each column is made up of 5 beads with the top, Heavenly, bead representing five and each bottom, Earthly, bead representing one.</p>
